= Glossary =

== A ==
; Activity
: A roadmap or project execution unit under milestones, often represented as a node with sequencing/prerequisite relationships.

; AD
: Active Directory, used for enterprise identity/group integration.

== M ==
; Module Code
: Claim value that gates access to specific application capabilities (view/edit/delete, etc.).

== P ==
; Plant Scope
: Authorization and data-visibility boundary tied to user membership in specific plants.

; Project Snapshot
: Project-local copy of selected template roadmap structures at registration time.

== R ==
; Roadmap Template
: Master planning structure defined in template tables and copied into project context.

== S ==
; SignalR
: Real-time communication framework integrated primarily in web UX components.

; SYS_GUID-style ID
: Oracle-generated GUID-like identifier often stored in VARCHAR2 columns for operational entities.

== J ==
; JWT
: JSON Web Token used by Pulse.Api bearer authentication.

